'''Arrianya Bel Iblis''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] who served the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and was the wife of the powerful [[Corellia/Legends|Corellian]] [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]].

==Biography==
The daughter of a well-off Core family, Bel Iblis supported [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] for the stabilization he brought to the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core Worlds]]. This drove a wedge between the married couple, who often argued over Palpatine's use of power. She, along with the Bel Iblis children, perished on [[Anchoron]] when a bomb meant for her husband detonated at the [[Treitamma Political Center]].

It was this deliberate act of assassination that drove Garm Bel Iblis into fully backing the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] and even becoming one of the Rebellion's more prominent leaders.

